text.__SUMMARY__: Conus harlandi is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails and their allies.Like all species within the genus Conus, these snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans, therefore live ones should be handled carefully or not at all.
text.Distribution: This species occurs in the Caribbean Sea off Belize and Honduras.
text.Description: The maximum recorded shell length is 36 mm.
text.Habitat: Minimum recorded depth is 12 m. Maximum recorded depth is 18 m.
